<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-3235] Restarting a bundle with  a jetty endpoint also stops connector for other jetty endpoints (in different bundles)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-3235</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Scenario: I create two simple routes in different bundles:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;route id=&quot;jettyRoute1&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;from uri=&quot;jetty:&lt;a href=&quot;http://0.0.0.0:15000/jetty?matchOnUriPrefix=true&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://0.0.0.0:15000/jetty?matchOnUriPrefix=true&lt;/a&gt;&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;log:nl.example.jetty.jetty1?showAll=true&amp;amp;level=INFO&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/route&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and (the other bundle):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;route id=&quot;jettyRoute2&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;from uri=&quot;jetty:&lt;a href=&quot;http://0.0.0.0:16000/jetty?matchOnUriPrefix=true&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://0.0.0.0:16000/jetty?matchOnUriPrefix=true&lt;/a&gt;&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;log:nl.example.jetty.jetty2?showAll=true&amp;amp;level=INFO&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/route&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I go to &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:15000/jetty&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:15000/jetty&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:16000/jetty&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:16000/jetty&lt;/a&gt; I get both log message in my log. My routes are working. However when I restart one of those bundles both jetty servers are killed and only one is restarted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also &lt;a href=&quot;http://servicemix.396122.n5.nabble.com/Jetty-connector-stops-unexpectedly-td3208647.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://servicemix.396122.n5.nabble.com/Jetty-connector-stops-unexpectedly-td3208647.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows Vista, Linux (CentOS release 5.5)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
